@node Main "Noel_Q - Documentation"

                              'Noel_Q' 1.14

                           by Charles-N. Jacob

  'Noel_Q' is a Workbench @{" game " link play} that is played like 'Solo' or 'Hi-Q'.
You play by jumping a peg to an empty space either horizontally or
diagonally, and depending if you play the @{" Normal " link play} or @{" Inverted " link play}
game, that peg must go over another peg (or empty space in the
Inverted game). In the @{" Normal " link play} game, the intermediate peg (the one
that was jumped over) will be removed. In the @{" Inverted " link play} game, the
intermediate empty space will be replaced by a peg.

  The goal is to remove all the pegs, leaving only one on the board.
If you play the @{" Inverted " link play} game, you start with one peg and you try
to fill the board leaving only one empty space.

  The main feature of the game is the 'Christmas theme': the shape of
the game board is patterned in the form of a Christmas tree, and the
pegs are randomly coloured, to simulate coloured lights or ornaments,
using the colour palette of the Workbench.

  When you get bored with the coloured pegs (or if you play the game
after Christmas :) there is an @{" option " link play} which selects the "white"
(normal) pegs.

  Have fun!

